---
import Snippet from "../../components/Snippet.astro";
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---
<DocsLayout title="Quickstart for local development and self-hosted deploys - Tako Docs" heading="Quickstart" current="quickstart" description="Get started with Tako in minutes: install the CLI, run local HTTPS development, and deploy your first app to your own server.">
  <h1 id="quickstart">Quickstart</h1>
  <p>This is the fastest path from "I just installed Tako" to "my app is live."</p>

  <h2 id="local-setup">Local setup</h2>
  <p>Install the CLI:</p>

  <Snippet code="curl -fsSL https://tako.sh/install.sh | sh" lang="bash" />

  <p>Verify installation:</p>
  <Snippet code="tako --version" lang="bash" />

  <p>From your app directory:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Install the SDK (Bun example):</li>
  </ul>
  <Snippet code="bun add tako.sh" lang="bash" />

  <ul>
    <li>Start local HTTPS development:</li>
  </ul>
  <Snippet code="tako dev" lang="bash" />
  <p>
    On your first <code>tako dev</code> run, Tako will ask for your <code>sudo</code> password to set up local no-port HTTPS
    and custom <code>*.test</code> URLs. This happens once and is reused for other apps.
  </p>
  <p>
    Open the URL shown in the terminal header. By default, Tako uses
    <code>{"{app}.test"}</code>, where <code>{`{app}`}</code> is your app name.
    The longer <code>{"{app}.tako.test"}</code> form is always available as a fallback.
  </p>

  <h2 id="remote-setup">Remote setup</h2>
  <p>Connect your workstation and deployment host to the same Tailscale tailnet. On each host (as <code>root</code> or with <code>sudo</code>), install the runtime:</p>
  <Snippet code='sudo sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://tako.sh/install-server.sh)"' lang="bash" />

  <p>Verify installation:</p>
  <Snippet code="tako-server --version" lang="bash" />

  <h2 id="first-deployment">First deployment</h2>
  <p>From your developer machine, add the server you set up in <a href="#remote-setup">Remote setup</a> to Tako:</p>
  <Snippet code="tako servers add <magicdns-name>" lang="bash" />

  <p>Run the following commands from your app directory.</p>
  <p>Initialize Tako config:</p>
  <Snippet code="tako init" lang="bash" />
  <p>
    <code>tako init</code> prompts for app name and production route, writes them to
    <code>tako.toml</code>, and updates <code>.gitignore</code> so
    <code>.tako/secrets.json</code> stays trackable.
  </p>

  <p>
    <code>tako dev</code> uses <code>{"{app}.test"}</code> by default. Add <code>[envs.development]</code> only when
    you want custom local routes.
  </p>

  <p>Deploy:</p>
  <Snippet code="tako deploy" lang="bash" />

  <p>Need every config option? See the full <a href="/docs/tako-toml">tako.toml reference</a>.</p>

  <p>Need framework adapter examples? See <a href="/docs/framework-guides">Framework Guides</a>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
